§7§oLarge gold-colred tamples floating on clouds. Follow the scanner. §o§7§oBreak blocks after finishing dungeon.

§fI was not expecting this! Out of the many creations that the banished testificates of the past left, there are organic beings.
From what I was able to collect, the banished society (if we can call it that) that formed on the aether islands was dominated by male testificates, who believed that they had greater mastery over magic than the females. 
In an act of rebellion, a group of powerful female sorcerers decided to unleash their destructive powers. Something, though, went wrong. The power they had unleashed was too much for them, and consumed them. 
They gained a type of immortality similar to mine, but completely lost their own will, turning into bloodthirsty warriors that only seek more enemies. 
It seems like the power of each individual has a certain limit that should not be crossed. 
Is this limit chosen by nature? Or can it be pushed further?
